</taxonomicName>
can easily be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[778,898,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bonamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis box="[778,898,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">B. lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the characters in the key above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1293,259,394]" box="[199,1097,295,322]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,295,321]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Body.</emphasis>
Male, 
<quantity box="[345,434,295,322]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="7.2">7.2 mm</quantity>
. Female, 
<quantity box="[541,676,295,322]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.55" metricValueMax="8.6" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="8.55" valueMax="8.6" valueMin="8.5">8.5–8.6 mm</quantity>
