<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,475,501]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named for the defunct train station named Jussaral, near the city of Angra dos Reis, which is the 
<typeStatus box="[358,406,511,537]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
locality. The station was active (
<bibRefCitation author="Giesbrecht, R. M." box="[773,962,510,537]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref79483" refString="Giesbrecht, R. M. (2015) Estacoes Ferroviarias, Available from: http: // www. estacoesferroviarias. com. br / rmv _ tronco / jussaral. htm (accessed 14 March 2020)" type="url" year="2015">Giesbrecht 2015</bibRefCitation>
) at the time the specimens were collected. The name is treated as a noun.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
